Using edge computing to alert traffic jams
2013/09-2014/02
Researcher
LIP6 laboratory
Description
Edge computing has many application scenarios in traffic conditions. On the one
hand, edge computing can realize real-time traffic prediction and road condition
report by rapidly processing vehicle sensor data. For example, on expressways,
edge device can collect and analyze the speed, acceleration, braking force and
other information in real time, and then predict the traffic flow, congestion degree,
accident risk and other conditions, and provide them to drivers, vehicle navigation
systems, urban traffic management centers and other relevant parties for use.
On the other hand, edge computing can improve the efficiency and reliability of
network communication in ITS. The Edge device can set up on the roadside,
process and analyze the information of vehicles and pedestrians in real time, and
quickly upload the processing results to the cloud server to avoid network
congestion and delay. At the same time, Edge device can also realize the
communication, collaboration and automatic driving among vehicles to improve
the safety and efficiency of the transportation system. In short, edge computing
has a wide range of applications in the field of traffic conditions, which can
provide real-time traffic information and prediction, and can also improve the
safety and efficiency of the traffic system. The objective of research is to alert
traffic jams by means of edge computing and calculate the influenced area.
Responsibilities
(1) Choose the appropriate edge device, clarify the data process flow; (2) design
the architecture for the prototype, conduct development and testing; (3) write
development documentation and user manual; (4) manage the project and give
the final presentation.
Achievement
In the first stage, we used smart phones as edge device to report the traffic
conditions of vehicles in real time. These edge devices will form a traffic jam area
network, and other devices in this area and nearby will receive traffic jam
warnings. In addition, we have developed a road condition query website,
where users can check the level of traffic congestion of a certain position on
the map.
Timatic Big Data Analysis Tool
2016.08-2017.01
Software engineer
International Air Transport Association
6
Description
IATA Timatic ( https://www. timaticweb2.com/ ) is the industry standard used
by airlines and travel agents to verify passengers travel document
requirements for their destination and any transit points. This project relies on
the massive data of global airline and travel agency document verification
within the Timatic system for data mining. By analyzing the document
verification failures cases of airlines , travel agencies, entry and exit
administrations of various countries, and visa processing agencies, it aims
to provide customized guide for those institutions to take preventive measures
in advance. The main content of the project is ( 1 ) modeling and cleaning
a large amount of source data, storing valuable data in a database; (2)
developing a query platform and providing API in different formats.
Responsibilities
(1) Participate in project specification and task planning; (2) Solve key issues
such as architecture and performance, as well as technical challenges
encountered during the development process; (3) Guide developers in
programming, host regular checkpoint and code review.
Achievement
I stored the huge source data file on HDFS. Then I used pySpark to process
the data and saved the result into MySQL database. In the end I created a
query platform based on e- chart ( an open source data visualization chart
library) . By providing data visualization from various dimensions for airlines,
travel agencies, entry and exit administrations, and visa processing agencies,
the bigdata analysis tool improved the work efficiency of our partners and
increased the market influence of Timatic products. Under my unremitting
efforts, the project launched and went live smoothly within the planned time
by collaborating with team across national. In addition, the introduction of
micro-service architecture and the deployment on AWS, initiated in this
project, were taken as a standard by the subsequent projects.
